A4.text: The Tenors (formerly known as The Canadian Tenors) are a vocal group consisting of Victor Micallef, Clifton Murray, Eduardo Aguirre, and Mark Masri.

A5.text: The Tenors were created by Jill Ann Siemens as a trio of Philip Grant, Paul Ouellette, and Ken Lavigne, debuting in 2004 in Victoria.

A6.text: In December 2003, Bühler became a member of the international musical quartet Il Divo along with Carlos Marín (Spain), Sébastien Izambard (France), and David Miller (United States).

A7.text: Their first album, Il Divo, became a worldwide multi-platinum-selling record when released in November 2004, entering the US Billboard at number four and selling five million copies worldwide in less than a year.
